course_metadata.title: Solar Energy Systems Design and Simulation

content_chunks.content: This course provides an overview of solar energy system design and simulation with a focus on photovoltaic (PV) and solar thermal systems. It covers solar energy fundamentals, system design, optimization, performance assessment, and case studies, preparing students to design, size, simulate and evaluate efficient solar energy solutions.

Technology for renewable energy system design and solar energy simulation - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in photovoltaic (PV) systems and solar thermal systems design using advanced simulation software platforms. Students will master Polysun, PV Sol, T Sol, and TRNSYS software for solar energy system design, PV system optimization, and solar thermal optimization applications. The curriculum focuses on practical solar energy simulation techniques for grid-connected PV systems, off-grid PV systems, and passive solar thermal solutions. Participants will gain hands-on experience with solar energy fundamentals, performance assessment methodologies, and life cycle assessment (LCA) for environmental impact evaluation. The program emphasizes solar energy economics analysis, EU solar energy policies compliance, and solar energy regulations implementation using cutting-edge design tools and simulation technologies for comprehensive solar energy solutions.
